The paper deals with distributed algorithms and communication networks, which are typical topics in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The objective of the paper is to study the applicability of local algorithms to a specific class of linear programs, which involves optimization and game theory, making the Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-category a likely fit as well. The paper also presents an approximation algorithm, which falls under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The problem studied in the paper involves bounded-size sets and neighbourhoods, which are typical features of the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves information theory and communication networks, which are relevant to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category.
